parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to slowly go down, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal slowly goes down
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the injection system throttle control sticks at idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a complete loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes do not respond when applied
the brake lines are rusted out
the vehicle has no other signs of rust.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Failure due to Rust and Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes due to rust and corrosion can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear brakes fail to function
the brake lines are rusted out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the foot-operated parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, especially on steep inclines, which can lead to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls or moves while parked
difficulty holding the vehicle on steep inclines
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion-Related Failure of Emergency Brake Cable System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion-related failure of the emergency brake cable system can cause the parking brake to fail, leading to unintended vehicle movement, which can result in accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked
rust or corrosion visible on the brake cable system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning throttle position sensor can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or collisions, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when towing trailers.
